howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.h7=Join Our Discord!
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p1=§bUtilityCraft§r is a progression and automation addon created by §eDorios Studios§r.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p2=It reshapes survival from the first day onward, giving early-game players new ways to gather resources and giving advanced worlds deeper systems to expand into.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p3=Start with basic tools, early resources, and mesh progression, then grow those simple loops into stronger materials and better production paths.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p4=UtilityCraft expands everyday survival with crops, tools, cobble generators, and useful blocks that help your world produce more while requiring less manual work.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p5=Machines, generators, batteries, and upgrades form the heart of automation, letting your base process items, route energy, and scale into larger factory setups.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p6=Liquid tanks give your systems reliable storage for liquids, making lava, water, and other liquid-based processes easier to organize.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p7=Mob grinding systems help automate drops and experience, turning combat resources into another part of your production chain.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p8=If you enjoy UtilityCraft, Dorios Studios also recommends §6Better Smelters§r for better ore furnaces, §bHeavy Machinery§r for large multiblock machines, and §dAscendant Technology§r for end-game technology and advanced machines.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p9=Join our Discord for updates, sneak peeks, betas, active discussion, bug reports, and direct community feedback.
howtoplay.utilitycraft.introduction.p10=Discord invite: §bAt2gzPtbNT§r
howtoplay.utilitycraft.getting_started.h1=Starting Out
howtoplay.utilitycraft.getting_started.h2=Crafting Essentials
howtoplay.utilitycraft.getting_started.h3=Flint Knife
howtoplay.utilitycraft.getting_started.h4=Crafting Recipes
howtoplay.utilitycraft.getting_started.h5=Sieve
