ui.utilitycraft:info.assembler=Crafts the recipe saved in a Blueprint. It consumes the matching items and §sDorios Energy§8, then stores the crafted result. The Blueprint is reused.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Materials§8: recipe ingredients.\n- §bBlueprint§8: saved recipe.\n- §cOutput§8: crafted result.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.autosieve=Consumes a sieveable block and §sDorios Energy§8 to roll resource drops. The installed Mesh is reused; its tier and modifiers control available loot, chance, and amount.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: block to sieve.\n- §bMesh§8: sieve modifier.\n- §cOutput§8: generated loot.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.autofisher=Uses §sDorios Energy§8 and a Fishing Net to generate fish, treasure, and junk. Water, flowing water, a bubble column, or a Sink must be within one block, including diagonals. The Net is reused and controls speed, rolls, loot tier, luck, chance, and amount.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §bFishing Net§8: fishing modifier.\n- §cOutput§8: generated loot.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.block_breaker=Uses §sDorios Energy§8 to charge, then breaks the non-liquid, breakable block directly in front. The resulting items drop into the world.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §8No item slots.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.block_placer=Uses §sDorios Energy§8 to place one valid block into an empty space directly in front. Each operation consumes one item.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Block Input§8: block to place.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.crusher=Consumes an item and §sDorios Energy§8 to process a registered Crusher recipe.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: material to crush.\n- §cOutput§8: crushed result.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.digitizer=Reads a shaped 3x3 crafting layout and consumes one Blueprint Paper plus §sDorios Energy§8 to create a reusable Blueprint. The items in the grid are only read and are not consumed.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Recipe Grid§8: 3x3 pattern.\n- §bBlueprint Paper§8: consumed paper.\n- §cBlueprint Output§8: saved recipe.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.electro_press=Consumes an item and §sDorios Energy§8 to process a registered Electro Press recipe.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: material to press.\n- §cOutput§8: pressed result.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.harvester=Uses §sDorios Energy§8 to harvest a square area in the direction it faces. The base area is 3x3; Range Upgrades enlarge it. Drops remain in the harvested area. With 4 or more Range Upgrades, they are pulled toward the machine.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §8No item slots.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.incinerator=Consumes an item and §sDorios Energy§8 to process a registered furnace recipe.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: item to smelt.\n- §cOutput§8: smelted result.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.induction_anvil=Repairs damaged tools, weapons, and armor directly with §sDorios Energy§8. Each durability point costs 10 DE before upgrade modifiers; the item remains installed while it is repaired.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: damaged durable item.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.infuser=Consumes the amounts required by a registered Infuser recipe plus §sDorios Energy§8. It combines a base item with a catalyst.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Input§8: base item.\n- §bCatalyst§8: recipe reagent.\n- §cOutput§8: infused result.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.magmatic_chamber=Consumes an item and §sDorios Energy§8 to produce the liquid defined by its recipe. The tank must be empty or already contain that same liquid.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Item Input§8: material to melt.\n- §cLiquid Output§8: produced liquid.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.xp_condenser=Stores up to §a256,000 mB§8 of liquid experience without consuming energy. Use the controls to move exact levels or the maximum possible amount between the player and the internal tank.\n\n§8Controls:\n- §c-1 / -5 / -Max§8: deposit player XP.\n- §a+1 / +5 / +Max§8: withdraw stored XP.\n\n§8Fluid I/O:\n- §9Input§8 and §cOutput§8 can be configured per face.
ui.utilitycraft:info.seed_synthesizer=Uses a registered seed, valid soil, and §sDorios Energy§8 to roll plant-resource drops. The Seed and Soil remain installed. Soil type changes the energy cost.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §9Seed§8: plant recipe.\n- §bSoil§8: energy modifier.\n- §cOutput§8: generated resources.\n\n§8Accepted Upgrades:\n§d §8(8), §d §8(8)
ui.utilitycraft:info.furnator=Consumes registered solid fuel to generate §sDorios Energy§8. One item is consumed when a new fuel cycle starts; its remaining energy is preserved if storage becomes full.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §vFuel Input§8: solid fuel.
ui.utilitycraft:info.magmator=Consumes §glava§8 from its tank to generate §sDorios Energy§8. Each mB of lava provides 100 DE, and generation pauses when energy storage is full.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §vLava Fuel§8: liquid fuel input.
ui.utilitycraft:info.solar_panel=Generates §sDorios Energy§8 during daytime. Output rises from dawn, peaks at noon, and falls to zero at sunset. It does not check for open sky and needs no fuel or I/O.
ui.utilitycraft:info.thermo_generator=Generates §sDorios Energy§8 only from a valid heat source directly below it and §gwater§8 in its coolant tank. It consumes 1 mB of water per DE; hotter sources increase output.\n\n§8Slots:\n- §bCoolant Input§8: water.\n\n§8Heat multipliers:\n- §8Blaze Block: 1.5x\n- §8Lava: 1x\n- §8Soul Fire, Soul Torch, Soul Campfire: 0.75x\n- §8Fire, Campfire, Magma Block: 0.5x\n- §8Torch: 0.25x
ui.utilitycraft:info.wind_turbine=Generates §sDorios Energy§8 at Y 20 or higher; no open sky is required. Base altitude is Y 63. Output gains 12.5% per 16 blocks above it and loses 12.5% per 8 blocks below it, up to the configured cap. Rain multiplies output by 1.5 and thunder by 2.25. No fuel or I/O is needed.
ui.utilitycraft:info.battery=Stores §sDorios Energy§8 received from a connected energy network and sends it back into the network automatically, limited by the battery tier's transfer rate.
ui.utilitycraft:info.receiver=Receives §sDorios Energy§8 wirelessly from Transmitters that match all three color channels, then sends stored energy into its connected local network at its transfer rate. Configure its channels with a Wrench.
ui.utilitycraft:info.transmitter=Stores §sDorios Energy§8 from its connected network and sends it wirelessly to Receivers within range that match all three color channels. Its tier limits range and total transfer per tick. Configure its channels with a Wrench.
